A man who allegedly lures women on Facebook, rape and kills them will appear at Mthatha Magistrateâ€™ s Court on Monday. The 28-year-old male who is believed to be a serial rapist and his 21-year-old girlfriend were arrested at Ncameni location and Ngcothi location over the weekend. It is alleged that the suspect invited women on Facebook posting a fake profile picture. Police Captain Khaya Tonjeni said he will then arrange to meet his victims in Qumbu sending them transport money via money market from two major retail outlets. Out of seven cases opened at SAPS Qumbu three were murder and four rape cases were reported. Tomjeni said the victims were from Alice, Duncan Village, Mthatha, Tabankulu and Mount Fletcher. According to reports, the women were strangled with a fishing rope and stripped of their clothing. TNA Reporter